sentences: John Evan (born John Spencer Evans; born 28 March 1948, in Blackpool, Lancashire) is a British musician and composer.

In 1970, he played as a session musician on Jethro Tull's Benefit album (where his acknowledgement reads: "...and John Evan, who played keyboards for our 'benefit'"), and was eventually convinced by Ian Anderson to leave school to become a full-fledged member of the band.
Evan departed Jethro Tull in July 1980, with the "Big Split" of the band.
He appeared in the 2004 DVD Jethro Tull – A New Day Yesterday:

He appeared in the 2004 DVD Jethro Tull – A New Day Yesterday:
He is best known for having played keyboards for Jethro Tull from April 1970 to June 1980.

Later on, Evan was attending college when he happened to recognize his then future bandmates on the radio with the song "Living in the Past", remarking years later that it stood out to him because of its quite unusual time signature for a pop song (54).
